  "en_snotes_asad": "I.e., finally and utterly - for, \"only on the Day of Resurrection will you be requited in full for whatever you have done\" (3:185). Since the pronoun \"them\" refers not only to the earlier sinners mentioned parenthetically in the preceding verse but also to those spoken of in verses 22-25, I have interpolated the word \"all\". Lit., \"those [alleged] partners of Mine\". Regarding the Qur'anic use of the term sharik (pi. shuraka') in connection with religious beliefs, see surah 6, note 15. Or: \"you were wont to contend [against My guidance]\". See in this connection surah 8, note 16. I.e., those who had availed themselves of the knowledge of good and evil which God offers to mankind through His prophets.",
